In contrast, Nvidia trades at a more reasonable 37.2x forward earnings, generates strong free cash flow, maintains high margins, and has a robust product pipeline including its upcoming Rubin GPU architecture. description: Meta Platforms is ranked No. 3 among Magnificent Seven stocks to buy for 2026. After pivoting away from its unprofitable Reality Labs division toward AI investments, Meta is seeing strong results with Q3 advertising revenue up 26% year-over-year. Despite being down 13% in three months, the stock trades at a discounted P/E ratio and has strong free cash flow to support its $70-72 billion 2025 AI capital expenditure plans.

title: Forget Stocks: This S&P 500 ETF Is Poised for Explosive Growth.
description: The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF (VOO) is positioned for strong growth due to its heavy concentration in tech and AI-exposed companies like Nvidia, Apple, and Microsoft, while maintaining diversified exposure across financials, healthcare, and industrials. With an ultra-low expense ratio of 0.03% and balanced sector allocation, VOO offers investors access to growth potential from the AI boom while providing downside protection if market leadership shifts.

title: Apple CEO Tim Cook Just Gave Nike Investors 3 Million Reasons to Cheer
description: Apple CEO Tim Cook purchased 50,000 shares of Nike stock worth nearly $3 million at $58.97 per share, nearly doubling his stake in the company. This marks his first open-market purchase since 2005 and signals confidence in Nike's turnaround efforts led by CEO Elliott Hill, despite the company facing challenges in China, tariffs, and Converse brand headwinds.

title: Buffett Calls These 4 Businesses Making Up Most of Berkshire Hathaway "Jewels"
description: Warren Buffett identified four core businesses as "jewels" driving Berkshire Hathaway's value: Apple, the property & casualty insurance business, Berkshire Hathaway Energy (BHE), and BNSF railroad. Despite selling 70% of Apple shares since 2023, it remains Berkshire's largest position. The insurance float has grown to $171 billion, BHE generated $3.73 billion in earnings last year, and BNSF produced over $5 billion in earnings. All four businesses continue to deliver strong returns as Buffett prepares to step down in January.

title: How to Review and Rebalance Your Portfolio
description: As 2026 approaches, investors should review and rebalance their portfolios based on a clear target allocation reflecting their risk tolerance and capacity. Rather than benchmarking against the S&P 500, focus on achieving your financial goals with appropriate volatility. Rebalancing can be done annually or when positions drift significantly, and a conservative portfolio component helps prevent panic-driven decisions during market downturns.

title: US Equity Outlook 2026: AI Growth Vs. Valuation Risks
description: The US equity market enters 2026 at a critical inflection point, transitioning from AI-led rallies to earnings-driven growth. While secular growth drivers remain intact, returns are expected to be more moderate and selective. Leadership is likely to broaden beyond mega-cap tech into industrials, energy infrastructure, healthcare, and financials. Markets will shift from narrative-driven to execution-driven investing, with valuations facing a ceiling that caps upside potential.

title: 5 "Magnificent" Stocks and 1 ETF That Are Must-Owns in 2026, According to Robinhood's Retail Investors
description: Robinhood's retail investors have identified five Magnificent Seven stocks and one ETF as top holdings for 2026. Nvidia leads as the most-held stock due to its dominant GPU market position, followed by Tesla, Apple, Amazon, and Microsoft. The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF (VOO) rounds out the top six holdings, offering diversified exposure to 500 leading U.S. companies with a low 0.03% expense ratio.

title: These S&P 500 Stocks That Skyrocketed in 2025 Are at Risk of a Sharp Correction
description: Among 102 S&P 500 stocks that gained over 30% in 2025, nine face downside risk exceeding 20% based on InvestingPro Fair Value estimates. These stocks, which surged 51.7%-149.5%, appear overvalued by 25.4%-45.7%. However, seven stocks with gains of 30.8%-84.9% still show upside potential of 20.3%-29.5%, presenting opportunities for value-focused investors.

title: Should You Buy the iShares S&P 500 ETF Before 2026, Even With the Stock Market at an All-Time High?
description: The article recommends buying the iShares Core S&P 500 ETF (IVV) heading into 2026 despite the S&P 500 being at an all-time high. The index has delivered a 10.5% average annual return since 1957 and is on track for 18% gains in 2025, driven largely by technology giants. The article emphasizes that historical data shows the index recovers from market downturns, and investors should maintain a long-term horizon of at least five years while considering dollar-cost averaging into the position.

title: Michael Burry Channels Warren Buffett In Molina Healthcare Stock
description: Renowned investor Michael Burry published a detailed investment thesis on Substack arguing that Molina Healthcare is a premier investment opportunity, comparing it favorably to Warren Buffett's acquisition of Geico. Burry highlighted Molina's focus on Medicaid programs, impressive growth potential, and high returns on invested capital, suggesting it has better business prospects than Apple. He noted the company's best-in-class loss ratio, expense ratio, and conservative accounting under CEO Joe Zubretsky, and believes MOH stock could be a generational buy if it falls below $100.

title: Down But Not Out: 5 AI Laggards From 2025 That Could Explode In 2026
description: Five stocks that underperformed in 2025 are positioned for strong growth in 2026. Apple, Adobe, Palo Alto Networks, Airbnb, and Target have lagged behind their peers but analysts expect them to lead in the new year due to AI initiatives, new product launches, supply chain improvements, and attractive valuations.

title: Investing Legend Warren Buffett Bids Adieu to Wall Street, While His Trillion-Dollar Company, Berkshire Hathaway, Enters a New Era
description: Warren Buffett steps down as CEO of Berkshire Hathaway on December 31, 2025, after 60+ years, with Greg Abel taking over. Despite being a net seller of stocks for 12 quarters, Buffett's value-focused philosophy and long-term approach nearly doubled S&P 500 returns. Abel is expected to continue this strategy while potentially expanding into technology and healthcare sectors, though some core holdings like Apple may be reconsidered.

title: How the Mag 7’s 2025 Laggards Could Turn Into 2026 Winners
description: Four of the Magnificent Seven stocks (Apple, Microsoft, Meta, and Amazon) underperformed the S&P 500 in 2025 due to massive AI capital expenditures, but analysts believe they could rebound in 2026. Amazon's AWS continues strong growth, Apple is increasing AI spending while benefiting from buybacks, Meta expects AI investments to pay off, and Microsoft's Copilot adoption is accelerating. All four stocks have bullish analyst ratings with significant upside potential.

title: Intel Investors Just Got Great News for 2026
description: Intel's 18A process node and expanded Arizona manufacturing capacity position the company to challenge TSMC's dominance in 2026. With strong demand for data center products and expected significant earnings growth, Intel could deliver stronger gains than the modest 10% analyst price target suggests, though valuation multiples remain elevated.

title: Trump's Tariffs — And The Art Of The Rebound
description: President Trump's April 2, 2025 'Liberation Day' announcement of sweeping 10% baseline global tariffs and reciprocal duties caused extreme market volatility, with the S&P 500 losing 9.5% over two days. However, a 90-day pause on reciprocal rates announced on April 9 sparked a major rebound, with the Nasdaq surging 12.2% that day. By year-end 2025, markets recovered significantly, with the S&P 500 up 17%, Dow up 13%, and Nasdaq up 21% for the year.

title: Purpose Investments Inc. Announces 2025 Final Annual Notional Distributions for Purpose Mutual Fund Trusts with December 15, 2025 Tax Year-End
description: Purpose Investments Inc. announced final annual capital gain and income distributions for its open-end exchange-traded funds structured as mutual fund trusts with a December 15, 2025 tax year-end. The distributions represent capital gains realized and income earned by the funds during the year, with varying distribution percentages across cryptocurrency and equity yield ETFs.

title: Here Are My Top 2 Stocks to Buy for 2026 and Beyond
description: Daniel Sparks recommends Apple and Berkshire Hathaway as complementary top stock picks for 2026 and beyond. Apple offers exposure to accelerating technology growth with 8% sales growth and 15% services segment growth, though it trades at a premium 33x forward P/E valuation. Berkshire Hathaway provides portfolio stability with $350+ billion in cash, conservative 1.6x book value valuation, and diversified operations, though faces leadership transition risk with new CEO Greg Abel replacing Warren Buffett.
